article.headline: Marist 83, Florida Atlantic 67
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. (AP) -- James Smith had 22 points and Jared Jordan added 16 points and 10 assists as Marist beat Florida Atlantic 83-67 Sunday. Marist (2-1) built a 12-point lead 6:41 into the game, but Florida Atlantic (0-4) responded with a 16-3 run over the next 6:36 to take a 21-20 lead. Derrick Simmons' fast break dunk 37 seconds before the buzzer put the visiting Owls up 35-34 at halftime. The game stayed close in the early minutes of the second half until a 3-pointer by Smith tied it at 51-51 at 14:12. From there, the Red Foxes used a 29-4 run over the next 9:52 to give Marist its largest lead, 80-55. Paul Graham led Florida Atlantic with 20 points. Will Whittington had 14 points for Marist and Ryan Stilphen had 12. Jordan and Whittington were honored in a pregame ceremony for surpassing 1,000 career points.
